    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors assessed for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level 3, attributable to the single-condition nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol; this shortfall is accepted given inter-laboratory reproducibility evidence and the prescriptive nature of the standard. All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percentage difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is judged sufficiently credible for its intended use in supporting the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated pedicle screw design. Decision: Accepted.",
